\begin_layout Subsection
Heterogeneous Fleet 2D Simulation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To validate the Lambda Field decision making framework in a mission,
 the concept was constructed and analysed as a 2D python simulation,
 deploying a full heterogeneous robot fleet encompassing four locomotion-types:
 A quadruped ,
 a drone,
 a submersible/surface robot and wheel driven rover.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The grid mimics a top down view of a real-world urban-rural hybrid environment.
 Each cell in the environmental grid will include an Bayesian occupancy along with other variables such as temperature,
 radiation and the presence of terrains such as water and stair cases which would be only accessible to specific locomotion types.
 Each agent will occupy one cell and start in unique locations.
 Additionally the types of terrain will be randomised each time the map is loaded into the grid to make each trial simulation is different.
 The will explore the environment using the D* Lite algorithm and will explore the grid to reveal cells in all cardinal and diagonal directions (illuminating a 3*3 square for the shared map).
 The decision making of the fleet will fall to a auction based task allocation based on the risk function of the lambda field integral of the area,
 such that suitable locomotion envelopes will investigate zones of the grid that would be most appropriate.
 Furthermore to accurately assess the use of the 2D simulation efficiency based risks such as battery depletion will be included for each agent.
\end_layout

