\begin_layout Subsection
Mission Planning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During autonomous deployment each agent was connected to the central GSC computer All robot IP addresses were allocated as threads in the Mission Planner [],
 allowing the system to pull the latitude,
 longitude coordinates from each vehicle and transmit the position as a floating path following point to other agents.
 Additionally each robot had a safety operator to ensure that the autonomous mission planner could be overridden to manual control at all times.
 The missions were originally simulated in Mission Planner to ensure agent stability and functionality as well as potentially diagnosing any fatal mission errors.
 The mission pipework involved arming and taking off each agent individually and ensuring stable flight and unique altitudes,
 before sharing GPS coordinates and passing way-points to following agents.
\end_layout

