\begin_layout Subsection
Summary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Initial simulation and physical testing showed that the system could handle a drone and a rover working together and that the fleet could pass coordinates through serial communication.
 The first demonstration highlighted key errors within the system,
 primarily communication latency and network interruptions.
 Firewall restrictions and out of date MAVLink software disable test flights due to the compromised GSC connection.
 Being aware of these dilemmas is invaluable experience for future real-world deployments as learning system debugging and consistent hot-fixing of deployed machines creates a foundation for the end of research deployment of a full fleet with the unified framework.
\end_layout

