 the robot fleet expanded from two agents to three including a drone at a higher altitude as the main convoy leader and was a success,
 however the speed of transmission between each message was reduced due to a packet loss and network dropout in agents.
 The issue came from weak internet connection,
 low quality transmitters and receivers that were in sub-optimal locations onboard the vehicles and aircraft.
 These complications have solutions that can be fully implemented and resolved in future experimental deployments.
\end_layout

